           <h2>Hangi</h2>
           <p>The Hangi is a traditional New Zealand Māori method of cooking food, using heated rocks buried in a pit oven. Meat and vegetables are placed in a basket and lowered into the pit, cooking slowly for hours. It is often prepared for large gatherings or feasts, and it's an iconic symbol of Māori culture.</p>

           <h2>Pavlova</h2>
           <p>Pavlova is a famous New Zealand dessert made of a meringue base topped with whipped cream and fresh fruits such as kiwifruit, berries, or passion fruit. It is often enjoyed during holidays and special occasions and is a point of pride for New Zealanders who claim it as their own creation, although Australia also claims it.</p>

           <h2>Fish and Chips</h2>
           <p>Fish and chips are a beloved takeaway food in New Zealand. The dish typically includes battered fish (usually snapper or hoki) served with thick-cut fried potato chips. It is enjoyed by Kiwis at beach outings or as a quick, comforting meal after a busy day.</p>
